net.automatalib.graphs

Interface MutableGraph<N,E,NP,EP>

  • Type Parameters:
    N - node class
    E - edge class
    NP - node property class
    EP - edge property class
    All Superinterfaces:
    Graph<N,E>, IndefiniteGraph<N,E>, Iterable<N>, UniversalGraph<N,E,NP,EP>, UniversalIndefiniteGraph<N,E,NP,EP>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCompactGraph, AbstractCompactNPGraph, AbstractCompactSimpleGraph, AbstractMutableGraph, CompactGraph, CompactSimpleBidiGraph, CompactSimpleGraph

    public interface MutableGraph<N,E,NP,EP>
extends UniversalGraph<N,E,NP,EP>
    A graph that allows modification. Note that this interface only exposes methods for extending a graph. If also destructive modifications should be performed, ShrinkableGraph is the adequate interface.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner
